#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSL (hue, saturation, lightness). Saturation: 0 means something on the grey axis; 255 means something between the grey axis and the most colorful color. This is different from ‚Äúchroma‚ÄĚ and should therefore get a different translation. Lightness: 0 means always black; 255 means always white. This is different from ‚Äúbrightness‚ÄĚ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:215
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>HSL-Saturation: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Lightness: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>To: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>Saturaci√≥ HSL: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Claredat: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HWB (hue, whiteness, blackness). The idea behind is that the hue defines the pure (maximum colorful) color. Than, white color can be added, creating a ‚Äútint‚ÄĚ. Or black color can be added, creating a ‚Äúshade‚ÄĚ. Or both can be added, creating a ‚Äútone‚Äú. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tint,_shade_and_tone for more information. 0% white + 0% black = pure color. 100% white + 0% black = white. 0% white + 100% black = black. 50% white + 50% black = gray. 50% white + 0% black = tint. 25% white + 25% black = tone. 0% white + 50% black = shade.
#: colordialog.cpp:229
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Hue: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>Whiteness: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Blackness: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"
msgstr "<p>To: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>Blancor: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Negror: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSV/HSB. HSV (hue, saturation, value) and HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) are two different names for the very same color model. Saturation: 0 means something between black and white; 255 means something between black and the most colorful color. This is different from ‚Äúchroma‚ÄĚ and should therefore get a different translation. Brightness/value: 0 means always black; 255 means something between white and the most colorful color. This is different from ‚Äúlightness‚ÄĚ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:242
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>HSV/HSB-Saturation: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Brightness/Value: "
"0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>To: 0¬į‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†360¬į</p><p>Saturaci√≥ HSV/HSB: 0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p><p>Brillantor/Valor: "
"0%‚Ā†‚Äď‚Ā†100%</p>"

